1.title: Sexual Healing
1.plot: In the premiere episode, Dr. V's new clients arrive with some bedroom issues. Meanwhile her husband takes a business trip, leaving her to take care of their four rambunctious boys all under the age of 7 on her own. Dr. Greg meets a new client with serious anger issues, and uncontrollably screams obscenities. Recently engaged to his partner of 23 years, he begins to worry about how his homophobic father will react to the news that they've finally decided to tie the knot. Dr. Eris counsels a couple on their dwindling sex life and realizes she is facing the same issue in...

2.title: Fear and Loving in Los Angeles
2.plot: After giving them some special homework, Dr. V listens to a recording of her clients, Georgie and Michael, in the bedroom. Watching four boys on her own at home pushes her over the edge. Dr. Eris wrestles with her stubborn client as she tries to convince her to let go of control in her relationship. At home, her experiment with tantric sex turns very awkward for her and her husband. Dr. Greg takes his client, Elizabeth, on an active therapy session in the car and is surprised by her obscene actions. He meets face to face with his dad, in what becomes a very ...

3.title: Carry the Weight
3.plot: Dr. V helps clients Georgie and Michael explore their kinky side with a trip to a sex shop. She sees new clients, a set of twin brothers, who have different sexual orientations. Dr. Greg sees a new client who despises overweight people. His sisters get upset when he tells them their abusive father may attend his wedding. Then Dr. Eris has an emotional breakdown in sex therapy with her husband. In the office, her client Kimberly has a revelation about her childhood and its effect on her marriage to Neil.

4.title: The Naked Truth
4.plot: Dr. Eris sees a plastic surgeon to find out if she will be able to breastfeed, meanwhile, her client Kimberly storms out of their therapy session with her husband Neil. In their final session, Georgie and Michael get some unique gifts from Dr. V to improve their sex life. Meanwhile, Dr. V takes her homophobic client Jacob and his twin brother to a gay nightclub. Dr. Greg struggles to work with his prejudiced client.

5.title: Under My Skin
5.plot: Dr. Eris assesses the aftermath of her clients Kimberly and Neil and meets with a new client, a Playboy Bunny. Dr. Greg takes his client Chris for an active therapy session at a "fat camp." Meanwhile Dr. Greg and his father, see a therapist. Dr. V worries that her breast implants perpetuate a stereotype, and also takes on a new client who thinks he's addicted to online dating.

6.title: Family Affairs
6.plot: Dr. Eris' client, a former Playboy Bunny, shows up to therapy in her ridiculous pajamas. Dr. Eris asks her husband to see a fertility doctor...with her mom. Dr. V airs her frustrations about her clients' made-up issues to her best friend Clayton. In an emotional sit-down with his father, Dr. Greg and his father decide to see a therapist together.

7.title: Episode #1.7
7.plot: A consultation with their fertility doctor brings Dr. Eris and Clayton some very troubling news. Dr. Eris is shocked to find out her Playmate client is suddenly engaged to a mysterious ex-boyfriend. In order to see her client, Shane, in action, Dr. V sets him up on a few dates and is mortified observing how he interacts with women. Dr. Greg's client shows up for couples therapy alone, and he takes her to task for it.

8.title: Final Thoughts
8.plot: Dr. V and Matthew take a trip to Palm Springs, but their attempt at a romantic getaway is hindered by her father's unorthodox babysitting while they are gone. Meanwhile, Dr. Eris and Clayton nervously await results from her fertility test. Dr. Greg receives a troubling message from his sisters on the morning of the wedding and as family and friends begin to arrive for the ceremony, Greg's nerves are at an all-time high.

imdb.title: LA Shrinks
plot: The professional and personal lives of dynamic experts are exposed as they counsel a wide array of clients at some of the top private practices in Los Angeles.::Bravo
